# Cordova plugins for Capacitor
capacitor-cordova-ios-plugins

# NOTE: `App/App/public/` and `App/App/capacitor.config.json` ARE
# tracked, despite being regenerated by `cap sync`. The Xcode
# project's pbxproj references them as required bundle resources,
# so a fresh checkout would otherwise fail to build until the
# developer ran `npx cap sync ios` manually. Committing the synced
# output makes the documented Mac flow (`pod install &&
# cap:open:ios`) work without an extra step. When `native-shell/`
# or `capacitor.config.ts` changes, `cap sync` will update these
# files; commit the diff alongside the source change.
